# Cline Rules for MCP Tool Usage

## MCP Tool Preferences
- For web searches and research tasks, prefer using Tavily search tools, and do not print the searched result.
- For file system operations within the project, use the filesystem MCP server
- For browser automation and web debugging, use the browser-tools-mcp
- For complex reasoning tasks, use the sequential thinking MCP
- To fetch a specific web page, use the fetch-mcp

## Auto-approve Guidelines
- Always auto-approve Tavily search tools for research tasks
- Auto-approve browser diagnostic tools (console logs, network logs, errors)
- Require approval for file system write operations outside the project directory

## Browser Paths
- Firefox: C:\Program Files\Mozilla Firefox\firefox.exe
- Chrome: C:\Program Files\Google\Chrome\Application\chrome.exe
